cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.SI, cs.LG. 

The paper deals with the Frechet distance, which is a metric used to compare two curves. This falls under computational geometry (cs.CG) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also introduces a new type of Frechet matching, which involves finding a locally correct matching. This could potentially fall under discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and machine learning (cs.LG) as it involves finding a matching that captures the similarity between the curves well. Finally, the paper presents algorithms to compute these matchings, which could fall under computational complexity (cs.CC) or algorithms (cs.AL).
